The paper deals with priority queues and their properties, which are fundamental data structures in computer science. The paper presents a new distribution-sensitive property called the time-finger property, which is related to the working-set and queueish properties. These properties are typically studied in the context of data structures and algorithms, which falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The paper also discusses the worst-case time complexity of various operations on the priority queue, which is related to the analysis of algorithms and complexity theory (cs.DM). Additionally, the paper introduces a new distribution-sensitive property that is related to information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.IT, cs.LG, and cs.AL, in that order.
